    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-20T09:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-20T09:56:00-05:00" n="665"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.115 Panay/163: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="93" xml:id="d665fn93">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-20T22:56:00+08:00"
                            >December 20, 1937—10:56 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 20—9:02 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0120. At press conference by General Harada, Japanese Military Attaché, he said
                    that Japanese boat which bombed <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi> at 1100, 12
                    December gave warning that the vessel was in dangerous zone, that <hi
                        rend="italic">Panay</hi> fired at Japanese troops on shore with main
                    battery, and that the army boat which boarded the <hi rend="italic">Panay</hi>
                    before she sank did not machine-gun the vessel before boarding. These statements
                    are entirely contrary to all evidence given by survivors to Court of
                    Inquiry.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
